        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 12:16PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 1216 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 6 miles east of Willisville
to near Garland. Movement was southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lerch, Norphlet, Stamps, Buckner, Mount Holly, Laughlin, McNeil,
Smithland, College Hill, Mount Vernon, Kenova, Medlock, McKamie,
Ebenezer, Canfield, Village, Magnolia, Cornelius, Smackover, and
Spirit Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 PM CDT for
south central and southwestern Arkansas.</instruction>
